'''''Pork Barrel''''' is a 1979 video game developed by George Blank and published by [[Ramware]] for the [[TRS-80]].

==Contents==
''Pork Barrel'' is a game about passing bills to win an election.<ref name="SG"/>

==Reception==
Jon Mishcon reviewed ''Pork Barrel'' in ''[[The Space Gamer]]'' No. 42.<ref name="SG">{{cite journal|last=Mishcon |first=Jon |date=August 1981 |title=Capsule Reviews|journal=[[The Space Gamer]]|publisher=[[Steve Jackson Games]]|issue=42|pages=36}}</ref> Mishcon commented that "If you can find people who'll pretend to be politicians with conscience, this game is fine. If you play to win, look elsewhere."<ref name="SG"/>

